DataElement.preferredName: Electrospray Ionization Instrumentation Loading Type java.lang.String
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A procedure used in mass spectrometry analysis. Means of delivering nonvolatile analytes into the gas phase for mass analysis. Best used on molecules which are charged in solution or readily accept a charge. Particularly well suited to the analysis of biomolecules.
